modules.description: This module implements integer-keyed maps using bit-level optimized Patricia tries, supporting efficient add, remove, find, and bulk transformations while prioritizing performance for sparse integer key spaces. Operations like iter and fold traverse bindings without key ordering guarantees, and conversions to sequences enable external processing when needed. It is particularly suited for applications requiring fast key existence checks and updates without dependency on key traversal order, such as sparse array representations or integer-identifier-based caching systems.
